children.subject: eecs106b usually got offered only in spring semester so I guess that's why it's not showing up on the draft for fall?

history.content:
Not sure about 152, though I'm hoping it's offered as I was planning on taking it. It's historically been the same class I think (152 and 252) so hopefully undergrads can also enroll.

106B shows up in the draft schedule now --https://www2.eecs.berkeley.edu/Scheduling/CS/schedule-draft.html

I asked the professor teaching it and he said he doesn't know. 252 is being offered which has shared lectures. Is there still a chance 152 will be offered? 

That and with 106b. I really hope both will be offered.
history.subject: If courses aren't in the draft schedule, does that mean they will definitely not be offered?
